sec.p:
Catchment population = ∑i∑j∑kAijk
Aijk=HijkMijk×Pijk
{i=agej=genderk=areaAijk=catchment population of a particular gender/age group in a particular area in2012Hijk=number of patients with a particular gender and age who visited the hospital A in a particular area in2012Mijk=number of patients with a particular gender and age who visited all medical institutions in a particular area in2012Pijk=number of populations with a particular gender and age in a particular area in2012}

The direct nonmedical cost consisted of transportation costs and nursing costs, and it was calculated using the following formulas:
Direct nonmedical cost=Direct nonmedical cost for visiting clinics+Direct nonmedical cost for hospitalization
Direct nonmedical cost for visiting clinics=∑m(Tm×α×Om)
{m=The identification number of patients who visited OPD clinicsTm=Average transportation costα=Crrection coeficient for transportation costOm=Frequency of visiting outpatient clinics(days)}
Directnonmedicalcostforhospitalization=∑n{(Tn×α)+(C×Ln×β)}
{n=The identification number of patients who was hospitalizedTn=Average transportation costα=Crrection coeficient for transportation costC=Average daily nursing costLn=Length of hospital stay(days)β=Correction coefficient for nursing cost}

For estimating the indirect cost, the human capital approach was used, which is based on the cost of lost workdays due to the disease. Indirect cost was calculated using the following formulas:
Indirect cost=Cost of lost workdays due to visiting clinics or hospitalization+Cost of lost income due to early death
Cost of lost work days of patients visiting clinics=∑m(Om×Rm×Dm)
{m=TheidentificationnumberofpatientswhovisitedOPDclinicsOm=Frequencyofvisitingoutpatientclinics(days)Rm=EmploymentrateofthatagegroupDm=Averagedailysalaryofthatagegroup}
Cost of lost work days of patinets hospitalized=∑n(γ×Ln×Rn+Dn)
{n=Theidentificationnumberofpatientswhowashospitalizedγ=ProportionrateLn=Lengthofhospitalstay(days)Rn=EmploymentrateofthatagegroupDn=Averagedailysalaryofthatagegroup}
Costoflostincomeduetoearlydeath=∑s[Mst×(12−m)×Rst+∑p=165−t{Mst+p×12×Rst+p(1+δ)p}]
{s=The identification number of patients who died of influenzat=Age at the time of deathMst=Average monthly salary at the age of t yearsm=month at the time of deathRst=Employment rate at the age of t yearsp=Time elapsed after death(years)δ=interest rateMst+p=Average monthly salary at the age of(t+p)yearsRst+p=Employment rate at the age of(t+p)years}
